    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 2: TURBOCHARGERS - REMOVAL</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REMOVAL</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
            <title>TURBOCHARGER REMOVAL</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using an open end wrench, loosen and remove oil feed supply tube nut located on top of
                    oil filter header. Remove and discard tube nut O-Ring (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600204">2.4</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two capcrews securing oil feed supply tube to top of turbocharger housing (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600205">2.5</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove oil feed supply tube and tube flange gasket from turbocharger assembly. Discard
                    flange gasket.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Cap oil feed supply tube fitting located on filter header.</para>
                <figure id="ef1600204" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5026" filename="../figeg5/EG5026.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2.4 Loosen Oil Feed Supply Tube Nut</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1600205" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5027" filename="../figeg5/EG5027.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2.5 Remove Oil Feed Supply Tube Capscrews</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove turbocharger oil drain tube as follows: (Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600206">2.6</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    )
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosen capscrew securing turbocharger oil drain tube retaining plate to crankcase.
                        Remove retaining plate and capscrew.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove two capscrews securing turbocharger oil drain tube to bottom of turbocharger
                        housing.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove turbocharger oil drain tube retaining plate together with turbo oil drain
                        tube, tube flange, two tube O-Rings and tube flange gasket from bottom of turbocharger assembly.
                        Discard both drain tube O-Rings (one on each end of drain tube) and flange gasket.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Cap
                    <emph type="bold">ALL</emph>
                    openings on turbocharger assembly. Use turbocharger intake cap set
                    <emph type="bold">ZTSE4296</emph>.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>If plastic caps are
                            <emph type="underscr">not</emph>
                            available, use duct tape to cover openings.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove four nuts securing turbocharger assembly to exhaust manifold flange. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600207">2.7</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove turbocharger assembly and gasket from engine. Discard gasket.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>SUPPORT TURBOCHARGER ASSEMBLY DURING REMOVAL OF MOUNTING HARDWARE TO PREVENT DAMAGE.</note>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="ef1600206" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5028" filename="../figeg5/EG5028.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2.6 Remove Turbocharger Oil Drain Tube</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1600207" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5029" filename="../figeg5/EG5029.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2.7 Remove Turbocharger</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
